title: A Poster for the Bill T. Jones and Arnie Zane Performance Piece "Secret Pastures"
Water window mural at the National Gallery of Victoria
The Marriage of Heaven and Hell
Crack Is Wack
description: This mural (1986) on handball court at 128th Street and 2nd Avenue was inspired by the crack epidemic and its effect on New York City. It was created as a warning and was initially executed independently, without City permission. The mural was immediately put under the protection and jurisdiction of the City Department of Parks and still exists.
